(22, 27, 9, 'Europeans Super League President Announcements!', '1619480393_president.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;President of Real Madrid Florentino Perez has threatened the UEFA with Super League as a substitute competition for the UCL. The only acceptable punishment is to kick Real Madrid out of the competition and banish Perez from any football related activity with immediate effect.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here you can read all the comments that President of Real Madrid and European Super League has made.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;If the players participating in the European Super League are banned from playing the 2022 World Cup in Qatar, we will create our own World Cup tournament. It is not a big deal.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;Football is the only sport in the world with more than 4 billion supporters and our responsibility within the big clubs is to meet the wishes of those fans.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;Football is going through a very tough situation, and the Super League will save the clubs financially.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&quot;The more competitive games, the more revenue clubs will generate and that is how they will survive this situation. The Super League is the solution.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&quot;We came to the conclusion that having the Super League instead of the Champions League, we could help alleviate the lost income.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&quot;Football has to evolve.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&quot;UEFA is a monopoly, they had to say what they said today.&rdquo;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&quot;It\'s over. Their monopoly is over. It\'s time for a new era.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&quot;They can\'t kick us out from our domestic leagues. Totally impossible.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&quot;Tebas? You have to show respect.&quot;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&quot;Manchester-Bar&ccedil;a will be more attractive than Manchester vs a smaller team.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 19:39:53'),
(23, 27, 9, 'European Super League: What is it and is it a good idea?', '1619480613_1681.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;In 2018, Germany&rsquo;s Der Spiegel reported on a European Super League after uncovering documents from Football Leakes outlining the competition. The idea was for the top European football clubs to break away from UEFA and start their own competition in 2021. The report by Der Spiegel sent shockwaves through football with clubs afraid they wouldn&rsquo;t be a part of the competition and fans feeling that another tournament would be too much in the landscape of football.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Plans outlined by Der Speigel claimed a 16-team tournament would begin as early as 2021. The competition would be similar to the Champions League except UEFA would play no part in the European Super League. Teams would play in a group stage followed by knockout rounds to claim a Europea Super League champion.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The format of the competition would favour some of the strongest, biggest clubs in European football. Of the 16 teams contesting the competition, 11 would be labelled as &ldquo;core founding&rdquo; clubs. These 11 clubs would be guaranteed their places in the Super League for 20 years. The clubs would be &ldquo;immune to relegation&rdquo;. The other five places would be made up of teams that could be relegated from the competition.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is claimed that a European Super League would usher in the end of the Champions League, the most popular cup competition in world football. It is also believed that a Super League would negatively affect domestic competitions as clubs would focus on the breakaway competition due to the amount of money at stake.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 19:43:33'),
(24, 26, 9, 'Football - Created by the Poor and Stole by  the Rich!', '1619483358_DTMxW80WsAAxf4u.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;The Fans have won.Football has been saved.&lt;br&gt;The cynical and greedy left powerless&lt;br&gt;as the European Super League is no more.&lt;br&gt;From banners of : &ldquo; Shame on you LFC &ldquo;,&lt;br&gt;&ldquo; Created by the poor, stolen by the rich &ldquo;, to widespread protests outside stadiums in a bid to save the beautiful game.&lt;br&gt;The fans have prevailed, once again proving that Football is nothing without the fans.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;It may seem like equality and meritocracy have been restored but that&rsquo;s not entirely true not until FIFA and UEFA continue to hold monopoly over the world of football.&lt;br&gt;Just like Perez and Agneli, these organisations should also be held accountable as the new champions league format all set to be implemented in 2024 isn&rsquo;t very righteous either.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Apart from creating a 100 extra UCL games in order to get more revenue, the reformed format will host 36 teams instead of the traditional 32 and those 4 extra spots will be taken up as follows :&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;* Ligue 1 will be allowed an extra spot for qualification.&lt;br&gt;* One spot will be allotted to a domestic champion of a smaller nation.&lt;br&gt;* And the remaining 2 spots will go to the highest-ranked clubs to have qualified for one of the other pan-European club competitions i.e clubs with a higher UEFA coefficient.This season it would&rsquo;ve been Spurs and Arsenal.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Similarly, the FIFA World Cup 2022 is being hosted in Qatar as all of a sudden FIFA finds it convenient to ignore the lack of human rights in the country just because a monstrous amount of money is involved in the project.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Don\'t get it wrong. While Florentino Perez and Andrea Agnelli are absolute money-chasers that do not understand football, the ESL saga does not make the UEFA/FIFA saints. Their interest in Qatar, claims that the country isn\'t as bad is bonkers. They stopped the big clubs mafia from getting money...because it\'s theirs - for now at least. The UCL budget having been announced to rise from 4B to 7B, UEFA/FIFA are the enemies of the story as well. They haven&rsquo;t saved football.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 19:44:20'),
(25, 26, 9, 'Super Six reaction since withdrawing from the ESL?', '1619483525_download.png', '&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Chelsea&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;As reported earlier this evening, Chelsea Football Club can confirm that it has begun the formal procedures for withdrawal from the group developing plans for a European Super League. Having joined the group late last week, we have now had time to consider the matter fully and have decided that our continued participation in these plans would not be in the best interests of the Club, our supporters or the wider football community.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Manchester City&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Manchester City Football Club can confirm that it has formally enacted the procedures to withdraw from the group developing plans for a European Super League.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Manchester Utd&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Manchester United will not be participating in the European Super League. We have listened carefully to the reaction from our fans, the UK government and other key stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We remain committed to working with others across the football community to come up with sustainable solutions to the long-term challenges facing the game.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Tottenham&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;We can confirm that we have formally commenced procedures to withdraw from the group developing proposals for a European Super League (ESL).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Chairman Daniel Levy said: &ldquo;We regret the anxiety and upset caused by the ESL proposal. We felt it was important that our club participated in the development of a possible new structure that sought to better ensure financial fair play and financial sustainability whilst delivering significantly increased support for the wider football pyramid&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Liverpool&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Liverpool Football Club can confirm that our involvement in proposed plans to form a European Super League has been discontinued.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In recent days, the club has received representations from various key stakeholders, both internally and externally, and we would like to thank them for their valuable contributions.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Arsenal&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The last few days have shown us yet again the depth of feeling our supporters around the world have for this great club and the game we love.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We needed no reminding of this but the response from supporters in recent days has given us time for further reflection and deep thought.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It was never our intention to cause such distress, however when the invitation to join the Super League came, while knowing there were no guarantees, we did not want to be left behind to ensure we protected Arsenal and its future.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a result of listening to you and the wider football community over recent days we are withdrawing from the proposed Super League. We made a mistake, and we apologise for it.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 20:05:32'),
(26, 27, 9, 'UEFA reacts to European Super League - full statement', '1619482519_download1.jfif', '&lt;p&gt;UEFA president Aleksander Ceferin spoke to media on Monday to respond to a proposed breakaway European Super League and present changes to the format of the European Champions League from 2024.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Here is his full statement:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;We began this project (new Champions League format) to modernise the competitions in early 2019, guided by the principle that it should be an exercise in inclusive leadership.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;At the start of this process, driven by a desire to evolve the UEFA club competitions into something better than the spectacle we know today, with the unanimous support of the European Club Association, ECA, we consulted widely across the game.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;Teams will always qualify and compete in our competitions on merit, not a closed shop run by a select few. That was our decision from the beginning, and any club and its fans should still have the dream of participating in the Champions League based on its results on the pitch.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;I cannot stress more strongly at this moment: UEFA and the footballing world stand united against the disgraceful, self-serving proposal we have seen in the last 24 hours from a select few clubs in Europe that are fuelled purely by greed.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;And not only football is united, all the society is united, governments are united, it\'s part of our culture, we are all united against this nonsense of a project.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;We have the English FA, Spanish federation, Italian federation, Premier League, La Liga, Serie A, but also FIFA, all our 55 member associations - unanimous in our opposition to these cynical plans, that are completely against what football should be.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;We urge everyone - from the millions of football lovers around the world, the world\'s media gathered on this call today, politicians and football\'s governing bodies - to stand tall with us, as we do everything in our power to ensure this never ends up in fruition.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;I wholeheartedly believe - we all do - that the changes we announce now (to the Champions League) are exactly the required next step in football\'s evolution.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;I would like to thank all the football family, meaning players, fans, coaches, national associations, leagues and clubs as well.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&quot;I would like to thank governments all around Europe, I would like to especially thank Prime Minister Johnson, President Macron, Vice-President of European Commission Mr Schinas, President of European Parliament Mr Sassoli, and all the other leaders around Europe who respect our fans, who respect our culture, who respect the values that are European values, not only football values.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 20:14:09'),
(27, 27, 11, 'The best XI of free transfers for 2021.', '1619482970_LINE-UP-2021-Free-Agents.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FREE TRANSFERS XI (4-3-3)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GK: Gianluigi Donnarumma&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The youngest goalkeeper ever to play for Italy &ndash; at 17 years and 189 days &ndash; has now matured into one of Serie A\'s most consistent performers between the sticks. The 21-year-old has been key to Milan\'s surge to the top of the table with four clean sheets in the league so far this season.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RB: Eric Garcia&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;A product of Barcelona\'s La Masia academy he joined Manchester City in 2017 where Pep Guardiola has been influential in his development. Blessed with an excellent reading of the game, and a superb positional sense, the 19-year-old has rejected a new contract at City and appears hungry for regular first-team football elsewhere.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CB: Sergio Ramos&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The knees might be creaking at the age of 34, but the Real Madrid and Spain&amp;nbsp;centre-back\'s mix of bloody-minded determination and charismatic leadership make him an asset to nearly any defence despite being at the back end of his career.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CB: Jerome Boateng&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Comfortable on both the right and left flanks the versatile Albanian full-back, 26, has been a dependable, and largely unsung, part of Bayern\'s defence since 2015. He may lack the eye-catching assists of attacking defenders but Hysaj uses the ball intelligently in possession.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LB: David Alaba&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Able to operate in defence or midfield the 28-year-old Austria international has spent a decade as one of Bayern Munich\'s most consistent and reliable players. With nine Bundesliga and two Champions League winners\' medals under his belt he has bucketloads of experience at the top level.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CM: Georginio Wijnaldum&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Dutch midfielder has been converted by Jurgen Klopp from a goalscoring attacker into an intelligent midfield workaholic integral to Liverpool\'s style of play. Largely unheralded, he is man for the big occasion as his two goals in Liverpool\'s famous 4-0 comeback win over Barcelona demonstrate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CM: Mesut Ozil&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;He turns 36 next May, and may lack the bite of old, but the Brazilian still has a lot to offer either as an efficient defensive midfielder or classy centre-back. Another player whose influence and quality may only be fully appreciated by City when he has actually left the club.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CM: Luka Modric&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;A cultured and experienced midfield playmaker who, despite his diminutive frame, still oozes class whenever he is on the ball. Part of the furniture at Real Madrid since 2012&amp;nbsp;the 35-year-old Croatian looks like he still has plenty of years at the top ahead of him provided injuries do not take their toll.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RF: Lionel Messi&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Should he stay or should he go? The transfer saga of 2020 looks set to dominate much of 2021 as well. Barcelona\'s greatest ever player needs no introduction. Since his debut in October 2004, Barca have won 55.9 per cent of their LaLiga games without Messi (won 66, drawn 39 and lost 22), compared to 73.7 per cent with him in the side (won 368, drawn 83 and lost 48).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CF: Sergio Aguero&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Injury problems appear&amp;nbsp;to be catching up with the 32-year-old Manchester City striker. On his day, there are few better natural finishers around. Aguero has more hat-tricks (12) than anyone else in the Premier League and is the highest non-English scorer in the history of the competition with 180 goals.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LF: Memphis Depay&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;A pitiful return of just two league goals in 33 appearances saw him jettisoned by Manchester United in 2017 but since then Depay has rebuilt his career and started to flourish. The Dutch forward has a respectable 62 goals in 154 appearances for Lyon in Ligue 1 and aged 26 is about to hit his peak.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 20:22:07'),
(28, 26, 11, 'Kane and Haaland are heading to Manchester this summer! ', '1619483648_TALKSPORT-Haaland-and-Harry-Kane.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;The two frontmen have enjoyed goal-laden seasons and are being &lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/football/853558/tottenham-harry-kane-erling-haaland-transfer-manchester-united/&quot;&gt;linked with big-money switches &lt;/a&gt;from Borussia Dortmund and Tottenham Hotspur respectively.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Spurs&rsquo; Carabao Cup final defeat to Man City on Sunday has once again led to calls for&lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/football/853558/tottenham-harry-kane-erling-haaland-transfer-manchester-united/&quot;&gt; Kane to quit the north London club&lt;/a&gt; in order to enhance his own personal ambition to win trophies.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Meanwhile, Haaland &ndash; who hit two against Wolfsburg on Saturday to take his Bundesliga tally to 25 for the season &ndash; is also a target for several clubs despite Dortmund insistent he will stay for at least one more campaign.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Murphy believes both strikers are destined for Manchester clubs &ndash; though he is unsure which of them will join City and who will move to United.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;I think the desire from the two Manchester clubs will be to get to the next level, especially Man United. I think &pound;100m [for Kane] from United or City is doable.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;I think Haaland will go to one of them and Kane will go to the other.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Spurs will be desperate to keep Kane but Murphy says he&rsquo;ll go if he makes it clear to chairman Daniel Levy he wants out.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Depending on the mentality of the footballer, if Harry Kane goes hard enough to Daniel Levy, he&rsquo;ll get his move,&rdquo; Murphy added.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Murphy puts Kane in the &pound;100m bracket, but Simon Jordan reckons the fee could be a sticking point as he claimed interested clubs may not be prepared to pay anywhere near that amount for the the England captain, who turns 28 in July.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Jordan said: &ldquo;I would think Daniel would look towards &pound;100m. I don&rsquo;t think the market will lend itself to &pound;100m, I think the market would lend itself to &pound;60m with add-ons, which will be of no interest.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Haaland, meanwhile, has been linked with a &lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/football/853558/tottenham-harry-kane-erling-haaland-transfer-manchester-united/&quot;&gt;big-money summer move&lt;/a&gt; to every top club in Europe after scoring a staggering 38 goals in 41 Bundesliga matches since joining from Red Bull Salzburg in 2020.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Man City, as well as United, are believed to be one of the many clubs interested in signing Haaland, who could be a replacement for soon-to-be&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/football/851384/sergio-aguero-man-city-chelsea-transfer-contract/&quot;&gt;out of contract star Sergio Aguero&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pep Guardiola admitted he was a a big fan of the Norway international,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/football/846544/erling-haaland-champions-league-record-harry-kane-ronaldinho-zinedine-zidane-ronaldo/&quot;&gt;who needed just 14 games to become the fastest player to score 20 Champions League goals&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;earlier this season.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 20:25:48'),
(29, 26, 11, 'Chelsea interested in Galactico\'s Raphael Varane this summer!', '1619484284_NINTCHDBPICT000638191176-e1614714725572.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;Chelsea have identified Real Madrid defender Raphael Varane as one of their top defensive targets this summer, reports claim.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;According to Sport Bild journalist &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/cfbayern/status/1383134096411525123&quot;&gt;Christian Falk, &lt;/a&gt;the Blues are interested in signing the Los Blancos defender, who has made his name as one of the very best defenders in Europe in his decade in the Spanish capital.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Varane, who has won four Champions League&rsquo;s with Real and a World Cup with France, has made 355 appearances for Real since joining the club from Lens in 2011.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is understood he is at the very top of Thomas Tuchel&rsquo;s transfer wish list this summer as the German looks to bolster his backline ahead of the 2021/22 campaign.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Reports last month suggested that Real are understood to be willing to sell the 27-year-old.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;However,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/football/831503/transfer-news-rumours-gossip-man-city-lionel-messi-varane-contract-man-utd-alaba-chelsea/&quot;&gt;Manchester United are said to be the frontrunners&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;to sign him.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Liverpool icon John Barnes, however, believes his former side are more suited to Varane over Chelsea and United.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Varane would be a fantastic signing for&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/sport/football/team/113209/liverpool/&quot;&gt;Liverpool&lt;/a&gt;. He&rsquo;s quick, he&rsquo;s a good defender and great on the ball so he would suit the way that Liverpool play and for Liverpool to sign him would be a fantastic piece of business,&rdquo; Barnes told&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://bonuscodebets.co.uk/&quot;&gt;Bonus Code Bets&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;He would strengthen any team in the Premier League but if he is leaving Real Madrid then there will be a lot of teams interested and a lot of competition to sign him.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Mbappe and Haaland are the answer to Liverpool&rsquo;s problems, but they would also be great for Real Madrid, Bayern Munich and every top team in Europe.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Attacking players are not Liverpool&rsquo;s immediate priority because they have Sadio Mane, Mohamed Salah and Roberto Firmino, who are fantastic players and the club are among the top scorers in the league while playing brilliant attacking football.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 20:41:19'),
(30, 26, 11, 'Haaland’s father hold talks with Barcelona and Real Madrid ', '1619484624_NINTCHDBPICT000640061151-e1615053293298.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;Erling Haaland&rsquo;s father, Alf-Inge, and his agent Mino Raiola have held talks with Barcelona and Real Madrid on the same day.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Speculation surrounding the future of the Borussia Dortmund star has only grown in recent weeks as we approach the summer.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Man City, Chelsea and &lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/sport/football/team/113099/manchester-united/&quot;&gt;Manchester United&lt;/a&gt; are among the Premier League teams who have been linked with bidding for his services.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Barcelona and Madrid are also emerging as serious contenders for the Norway wonderkid&rsquo;s signature, especially after Thursday&rsquo;s events.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Spanish publication &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/bombazo-mino-raiola-padre-haaland-11630578&quot;&gt;Sport&lt;/a&gt; posted pictures of Alf-Inge and Raiola arriving in Barcelona.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Their report also claims they were met at the airport by an assistant of Joan Laporta &ndash; who has just been elected as club president.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Raiola and Laporta are said to have a good relationship, but it remains to be seen if Barca have the funds right now.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Catalan club are in serious debt, with reports earlier this season claiming the figure is around &pound;1billion.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Just hours later, Raiola and Alf-Inge Haaland were spotted in Madrid for talks with Barcelona&rsquo;s rivals.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Haaland only joined Dortmund in January 2020, but has already scored 49 goals in 49 games.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;He has a release clause in his contract of &pound;68million, but that does not become active until 2022.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Transfer expert Fabrizio Romano confirmed both meetings took place and expects more clubs to sit down with Raiola over the coming weeks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;He wrote on &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/FabrizioRomano&quot;&gt;Twitter&lt;/a&gt;: &ldquo;The meeting between Mino Raiola, Erling Haaland&rsquo;s father and Joan Laporta has been positive. It was the first contact to discuss about the new Barcelona project &ndash; obviously there&rsquo;s nothing done or advanced, race will be long as many clubs are involved&hellip; Bar&ccedil;a are in.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Mino Raiola will meet/talk also with other top clubs in the next weeks&hellip; and Bayern M&uuml;nich are *not* in the race for this summer. Raiola also met with BVB this week to discuss about the price as Haaland&rsquo;s clause will be NOT valid in 2021, only in July 2022.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A separate tweet added: &ldquo;Confirmed. Mino Raiola is in Madrid &lt;i&gt;right now&lt;/i&gt; after leaving Barcelona on a private flight. There is also the Haaland&rsquo;s father with him.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;After meeting with Barcelona president Laporta, Raiola will talk today also with Real Madrid about Haaland deal.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Borussia Dortmund Michael Zorc sport director recently confirmed he has met with Raiola.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Yes, yesterday I spoke to Raiola. We&rsquo;ve made our intentions very clear&rdquo;, told SkyDe.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is thought that Dortmund will not sell Haaland for anything less than &pound;127million (&euro;150m).&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 20:49:09'),
(31, 26, 11, 'How Messi could hold the key to  Aguero’s future with  Barcelona', '1619484822_NINTCHDBPICT000644516949.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;Lionel Messi could hold the key to Sergio Aguero&rsquo;s next move after he leaves Man City, talkSPORT was told.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The City forward &lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/football/857199/sergio-aguero-man-city-confirm-exit-summer/&quot;&gt;will leave the Etihad Stadium&lt;/a&gt; after ten illustrious years with 257 goals in 384 games.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;He&rsquo;s won four Premier League titles, and likely a fifth this season, and ushered in a period of dominance for the Manchester club.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;But last night it was announced the 32-year-old would be leaving when his contract expires at the end of the season.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And South American football expert Tim Vickey thinks Aguero&rsquo;s future will be intertwined with that of Barcelona superstar Messi.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/who/lionel-messi/&quot;&gt;Messi&lt;/a&gt; is out of contract with the Catalan club this summer and there has been much speculation around his future.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Last summer, there were rumours of him joining Man City and Aguero was a big reason for that as Argentina duo are close friends.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;That appears unlikely now with Paris Saint-Germain another possible destination that could lure the pair together.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;There is an interesting little thing going on in Europe, Paris Saint-Germain perhaps, Barcelona perhaps,&rdquo; Vickery told talkSPORT.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;The reason it&rsquo;s both of those clubs has less to do with Aguero and more to do with Lionel Messi.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Messi and Aguero are old mates. They roomed together all the way back in 2005 when Argentina won the Under-20 World Cup and they struck up a real relationship.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;They&rsquo;ve been mates ever since. When they play for the national team you see that relationship and they are on a wavelength.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve always wanted to seem them together at club level and I think PSG reportedly being interested is a way of trying to get Messi. Barcelona being interested is a way of perhaps keeping Messi.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;It depends how much money you&rsquo;re going to pay him. Are you really going to pay top dollar? Especially if you&rsquo;re in the financial situation Barcelona are in.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Aguero first met Messi back when they were teenagers preparing for the Under-20 World Cup.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;But he later admitted to not knowing who he was, despite being at Barcelona.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;We were all staying together, my age group and his age group.&rdquo; Aguero told &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p50g7kV3o1o&amp;amp;ab_channel=SkySportsRetro&quot;&gt;Sky Sports&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;I remember there was a kid there I&rsquo;d seen on TV who was at Barcelona.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;We were all sat round a table, Garay, Leo, Formica and myself. Leo was opposite me and Garay asked about some trainers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Leo says &lsquo;I got them from the United States&rsquo;. So then I started to think to myself &ndash; United States? Does he play in the United States?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Then I said to him quietly, &lsquo;what&rsquo;s your name again?&rsquo; And he says &lsquo;Leo&rsquo;. I said &lsquo;no, what&rsquo;s your name?&rsquo;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;He said &lsquo;Lionel Messi&rsquo;. The other two looked at me and said &lsquo;you don&rsquo;t know who he is?&rsquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;They all laughed and I thought &lsquo;you&rsquo;re that kid&rsquo; and it clicked. That&rsquo;s where we first became friends.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 20:53:42'),
(32, 26, 11, 'Beckham believes selling Miami to Messi ‘not a difficult pitch’', '1619485148_NINTCHDBPICT000566018491-e1616578306153.jpg', '&lt;p&gt;David Beckham insists he would have no trouble pitching an Inter Miami transfer to Cristiano Ronaldo, Neymar or Lionel Messi.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The MLS club, co-owned by Beckham and coached by Phil Neville, have attracted experienced players such as Blaise Matuidi and Gonzalo Higuain since their inception in 2018.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Inter Miami have also raided England for Ryan Shawcross and former &lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/sport/football/team/113203/arsenal/&quot;&gt;Arsenal&lt;/a&gt; defender Kieran Gibbs in the past month.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And Beckham is confident his club can attract the world&rsquo;s biggest players, including Ronaldo, Neymar and Messi.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Asked what his sales pitch would be to those three megastars, Beckham told ESPN: &ldquo;To be honest, it&rsquo;s not a difficult pitch. You just say &lsquo;Miami&rsquo; and they&rsquo;re like, &lsquo;okay!&rsquo;&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Messi and Juventus forward Ronaldo are in the twilight years of their career.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Meanwhile, Neymar, 29, still has hopes of winning the Champions League with Paris Saint-Germain after falling short in last year&rsquo;s final against Bayern Munich.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Earlier this month, &lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/football/843317/david-beckham-cristiano-ronaldo-lionel-messi-inter-miami/&quot;&gt;Beckham revealed Inter Miami were targeting players with the stature of Messi and Ronaldo&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Without a doubt, those are the type of players that we aspire to bring to our club. I think that the fans would really appreciate that,&rdquo; he said.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;But, you know, as owners, we want players here that are driven, that want to win, and that&rsquo;s our priority.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;With Blaise Matuidi and Gonzalo Higuain, these are players that we feel add to the glitz and the glamour of what the club is.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Going forward, we also want to bring other players in if we have the opportunity to bring some great names in, you obviously mentioned Leo and Cristiano.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;They&rsquo;ve been at the top of their game for the last 15 years because of hard work. Sir Alex Ferguson was a master at it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;He didn&rsquo;t always bring in the best player in the world. He didn&rsquo;t always bring in the top player. He bought the right player for the club.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;And I think that that&rsquo;s the one thing that I take into our club, is the player has to be right.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;However, it doesn&rsquo;t look like Messi&rsquo;s time at the club is over yet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Barca are desperate to keep hold of him with newly elected president Joan Laporta promising to do his best to get him to stay &ndash; and club legend Rivaldo thinks that may have swung it in their favour.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Barcelona are massively improving in the last few weeks capitalising on &lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/football/853704/lionel-messi-stats-2021-barcelona-real-atletico-madrid-table/&quot;&gt;Lionel Messi&rsquo;s superb form&lt;/a&gt; and the election of a new president,&rdquo; he told &lt;a href=&quot;https://betting.betfair.com/football/rivaldo/&quot;&gt;Betfair&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Messi looks much more connected and happier since &lt;a href=&quot;https://talksport.com/football/846352/joan-laporta-barcelona-messi-contract-beckham-ronaldinho/&quot;&gt;Joan Laporta&rsquo;s arrival&lt;/a&gt; &ndash; a president he knows well.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;For that reason, I&rsquo;m starting to believe more and more that Messi might reach an agreement with the new board and sign a new contract to stay at the club for a few more years.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;Messi had a confidence boost with the new president election &ndash; someone he has a good connection with &ndash; raising the chances of him considering to stay for a bit longer.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Inter Miami joined MLS last season in a coronavirus hit campaign.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There has already been a change in head coach, though, with Neville appointed by his old Manchester United teammate.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The former&amp;nbsp;defender led the England Women&rsquo;s side to a 2019 World Cup semi-final during his three-year spell in charge.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Neville&rsquo;s squad contains the likes of Matuidi, Higuain and Shawcross, while West Brom&rsquo;s Gibbs will be heading to Miami at the end of the Premier League season.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;He confirmed the news on Instagram, writing: &ldquo;Extremely excited to be starting the next chapter of my career with @InterMiamiCF this summer!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;I look forward to embracing a new culture and a new challenge in South Florida. I&rsquo;m really impressed by the vision of the Club, and can&rsquo;t wait to play in front of The Siege, Southern Legion, and Vice City 1896.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&ldquo;In the meantime, my focus and commitment remains with West Brom. I will continue to give 100% for the team, as I have done since I signed, until the end of the season.&rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;', 1, '2021-04-26 20:57:39');

